Description: Small pottery vessel, roughly vase shaped but made with irregular bag-shaped body which tapers in to form a stout neck. The base is roughly flattened. A small hole has been inserted in the centre but except for the hole the interior was not hollowed out. The hole extends almost to the full length of the body to a depth of 2.2 cm with a diameter of 0.5 cm. The original surface had a cream slip and was well smoothed.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E12.1, upper layers
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 185)
